observations.recommendation:
For the proper management and handling of Inventory, we recommended the following:
1.	That the Management require the concerned personnel to conduct periodic physical inventory count of supplies and submit Report on Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI) not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively;
2.	That the General Services Officer (GSO) maintain supplies stock cards for each type of supplies and reconcile these with the ledger card maintained in the Accounting Office;
3.	Discrepancies between physical and book inventories must be investigated and cleared immediately; and
4.	After the physical inventory count, the Inventory Committee shall reconcile the results of the count with the accounting records.

That the Inventory Committee conduct the required annual physical count of each category of PPE as of December of every year. The actual count may be undertaken any month during the current year, but has to be updated at year-end. This procedure is a must in order to know the physical existence of the PPE and their conditions; and to identify, segregate and reclassify unserviceable assets;
Reconciliation of the result of the count with the accounting records is to be undertaken to effect the necessary adjustments; and to pinpoint responsibility/accountability/liability for any missing PPEs;
The RPCPPE shall be submitted to the Audit Team within the prescribed deadline; and
That the Municipal Accountant maintain/update the subsidiary ledgers, PPE ledger cards and, the GSO/Municipal Treasurer maintain Stock Cards and Property Cards for proper control and monitoring of the PPEs and for facility in identifying them.
